Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.92,0:01:34.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,\ngood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.29,0:01:37.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Those who forge their own destiny.\NThose who balk at their own destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.66,0:01:43.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Time visits all men equally and imposes\non them a choice for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.03,0:01:47.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When the final letter entrusted\nto the young man is read,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.93,0:01:51.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...what future will that\nbring about for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.00,0:01:57.01,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,352)}Act 21:\NThe Golden Boy's True Identity
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.91,0:02:03.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count! There's something that\NI have to talk to you about!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.35,0:02:04.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.25,0:02:11.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Could he have left Paris already?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.73,0:02:25.79,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As the price of Danglars Bank stocks hits\ntrading limit lows day after day,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.90,0:02:29.14,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...customers are swarming the teller windows\nto withdraw their savings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.88,0:02:31.60,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At this time, the whereabouts\nof the bank management,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.71,0:02:33.80,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...including Monsieur Danglars,\nare unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.95,0:02:35.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You bunch\nof idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.78,0:02:38.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have your precious treasure\nright here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.88,0:02:41.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make a profit off of any situation,\neven bad ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.59,0:02:45.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All I need is this stake money,\nand I'll be good as gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.03,0:02:49.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,With five trillion francs at my disposal,\NI can win any speculation war.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.76,0:02:51.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then, which stock\nshould I start with?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.43,0:02:55.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, I can't stand how inefficient\nthis is without Michelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.91,0:03:03.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Good afternoon to you,\NMonsieur Danglars.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.51,0:03:06.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Monte Cristo!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.42,0:03:14.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I-I was under the impression that I had bought\nout all the seats on this special flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.19,0:03:18.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have come from Paris.\NI was forced to chase you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.66,0:03:20.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that wasn't necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.69,0:03:23.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I had hoped to have you\naccommodate me with funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.13,0:03:26.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Five trillion francs.\NIn cash, right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.60,0:03:28.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,F-Five trillion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.87,0:03:34.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,According to my contract with you, there\nis no upper limit to my line of credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.57,0:03:36.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you haven't forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.84,0:03:40.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't. Believe me,\NI haven't forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.01,0:03:45.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But you've caught me at a bad time.\NI'm traveling, so I'm not carrying any...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.42,0:03:48.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But surely you are carrying cash\nin that case, are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.32,0:03:48.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.85,0:03:50.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come, now. Give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.99,0:03:53.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't possibly!\NThis is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.56,0:03:54.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.26,0:03:57.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.40,0:03:59.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.90,0:04:06.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd turned around and gone home quietly,\nyou wouldn't have had to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.11,0:04:08.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.44,0:04:11.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna have to do something\nabout the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.82,0:04:23.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,B-But you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.66,0:04:31.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You are as full of avarice\nas you ever were.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.13,0:04:34.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't changed one iota\nfrom the old days.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.20,0:04:36.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.70,0:04:39.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look closely at my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.74,0:04:41.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Think back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.94,0:04:47.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Think back and remember the face of the man\nthat you consigned to oblivion 25 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.88,0:04:50.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Remember the face\nof your friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.42,0:04:53.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...whom you incriminated with your\nfalse accusations against him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.45,0:05:00.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,E-Edmond Dantes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.63,0:05:05.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond... Take good care\nof this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.53,0:05:09.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You will be the next\ncaptain of the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.20,0:05:12.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.31,0:05:18.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to see me,\NActing Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.44,0:05:23.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Danglars, these figures in the\ntrade ledgers just don't add up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.11,0:05:29.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, um... When we were docked at\NAlpha Centauri last month, they...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.15,0:05:31.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen!\NThis is embezzlement!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.26,0:05:35.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll overlook it this one time.\NBut if I ever see it happen again, I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.63,0:05:43.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You think you're\NCaptain already, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.60,0:05:47.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Three cheers\nfor Edmond!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.24,0:05:50.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mercedes is head over heels\nfor that boy, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.64,0:05:54.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to him, all the other guys who hit\non her are no better than garbage! Garbage!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.38,0:06:00.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, Edmond and Mercedes are finally having\ntheir engagement party next week, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.42,0:06:02.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.72,0:06:05.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be praying for those two\nto live happily ever after!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.12,0:06:07.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.56,0:06:10.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.40,0:06:13.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's no such thing\nas a perfect man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.83,0:06:16.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Know what I mean, Fernand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.50,0:06:23.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Every man ought to have\na flaw or two. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.41,0:06:24.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What're you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.74,0:06:30.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When Captain Leclere died, he entrusted\NEdmond with a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.48,0:06:33.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you suppose\nwas in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.75,0:06:37.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Word has it that it was a secret document\naddressed to the dissident faction in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.62,0:06:41.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Pretty interesting,\nisn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:44.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if we were to humbly bring it\nto the government's attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.26,0:06:46.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...what do you suppose would\nhappen to Edmond?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.10,0:06:50.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.40,0:06:52.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.74,0:06:55.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mercedes! This is all\nsome kind of mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.74,0:06:57.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry\nabout me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.28,0:07:02.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.82,0:07:07.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This sure brings back\nmemories...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.99,0:07:12.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of those days aboard the Pharaon, when we\nall sailed the sea of stars together...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.99,0:07:14.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.47,0:07:25.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going\nto do to me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.71,0:07:31.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you think that I was the one who\nset you up, you've got it all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.38,0:07:33.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I-It was Fernand!\NHe did it to get your woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.51,0:07:37.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I only told him about the letter\nbecause he was so depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.78,0:07:41.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That it would be funny\nif we reported the letter...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.32,0:07:44.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I only meant it\nas a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.60,0:07:58.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Out of jealousy and unjustified resentment,\nyou sent an innocent young man to prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.90,0:08:00.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is that not\nthe case?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.44,0:08:04.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong!\NIt wasn't like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.74,0:08:09.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You were nothing but an\nirritation to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.78,0:08:11.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It made me sick\nto look at you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.72,0:08:18.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have any reason! I just wanted\nto get Edmond Dantes out of my sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.33,0:08:27.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Those are...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.87,0:08:30.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!\NThis is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.84,0:08:33.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate your candor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.51,0:08:36.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now, accept my humble way\nof repaying you for your bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.75,0:08:43.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.58,0:08:46.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Edmond!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.92,0:08:52.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Rejoice. Everything that\nyou touch turns to gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.19,0:08:54.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.43,0:09:01.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.65,0:09:17.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Wait a minute!\NDon't leave me here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.52,0:09:23.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please!\NCome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.03,0:09:35.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And that is one...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.58,0:09:46.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Find somewhere else\nto sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.18,0:09:49.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.25,0:09:53.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've been waiting for him all this time?\NGee, what a tenacious young man you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.62,0:09:55.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mock me!\NI'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.15,0:09:59.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"I simply must speak with the Count!"\NIs that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.92,0:10:02.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lay off! You're just his lackey,\nso this is none of your business!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.03,0:10:08.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gosh, and here I was about to\ntell you where the Count is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.20,0:10:11.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, wipe that look\noff your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.94,0:10:15.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Count's in space.\NRight about now, I bet Danglars is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.04,0:10:16.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.91,0:10:21.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can try to put up a fight all you want,\nbut it won't do you any good at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.85,0:10:24.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're the Count's right-hand man,\naren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.52,0:10:27.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Why don't\nyou stop him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.32,0:10:30.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you understand\nhow the Count really feels?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.59,0:10:31.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.82,0:10:34.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk like you\nknow everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.46,0:10:35.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't YOU understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.33,0:10:38.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That he has to get revenge\nin spite of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.90,0:10:41.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That he can't forget the past\nin spite of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.47,0:10:43.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He has to do all that\nin spite of how he feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.70,0:10:52.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe so, but there's something that I have to\ntell the Count before he loses everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.25,0:10:59.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They say that Villefort's first trial hearing\nis gonna be tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.98,0:11:03.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now, it's time for little boys\nto be in bed! Go on home!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.30,0:11:16.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, this kid might be tougher\nthan you think he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.08,0:11:28.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This trial in the cases of the poisoning\nin the Villefort household,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.31,0:11:31.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...as well as the attempted murder of the Count\nof Monte Cristo, will now come to order.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.22,0:11:36.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to make a statement\nbefore we begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.45,0:11:38.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My actions were not\nout of self-interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.06,0:11:42.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I did what I did in order to protect\nthe peace and public order of Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.49,0:11:45.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As such, I plead not guilty with no\nshame or remorse for my actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.83,0:11:48.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and will be acting\nas my own attorney.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.44,0:11:54.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can't come in if you don't\nhave a permit! Go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.01,0:11:58.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This poisoning was the result of the attempt\nby Héloïse, Monsieur Villefort's second wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.08,0:12:02.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...to poison her stepdaughter Valentine\nin order to get at her inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.55,0:12:06.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In addition to falsely accusing the Count\nof Monte Cristo for these murders,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.12,0:12:08.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...Monsieur Villefort also\nattempted to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.59,0:12:11.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than being motivated\nby love for his wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.22,0:12:13.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...these acts were an attempt by Crown\NProsecutor Villefort to protect his...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.83,0:12:15.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.26,0:12:19.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Monte Cristo is a disruptive element\nwho is throwing Paris into turmoil!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.63,0:12:22.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Another possibility is that he is a spy\nsent here by the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.40,0:12:31.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As a faithful officer of the court, I call for the\nimmediate arrest of the Count of Monte Cristo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.55,0:12:37.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is that really the case,\NI wonder?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.12,0:12:38.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you implying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.42,0:12:42.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to call a witness who can shed\nsome light on the defendant's past.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.50,0:12:53.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Order in the courtroom!\NWitness, state your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.10,0:12:56.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Andrea Cavalcanti.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.84,0:12:59.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Admittedly, it is\nan alias.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.50,0:13:01.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The witness will answer\nthe question truthfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.21,0:13:05.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the orphanage,\NI was called Benedetto.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.28,0:13:08.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know\nmy real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.15,0:13:13.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see here that you were known to the public\nas the head of a notable aristocratic family?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.32,0:13:17.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, stop that. I'm not an aristocrat.\NI'm nothing of the sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.19,0:13:21.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was abandoned as an infant,\nraised in an orphanage,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.76,0:13:24.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and once I got out, I did\neverything under the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.90,0:13:28.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Larceny. Arson.\NAnd even murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.63,0:13:32.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And what does this have to\ndo with the case at hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.40,0:13:37.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A great deal. I've come here today to tell\nthe story of the secret behind my birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.38,0:13:39.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Quit your joking!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.78,0:13:42.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Order in the courtroom!\NContinue with your testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.82,0:13:49.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was born in Auteuil. In the estate that the\NCount of Monte Cristo now uses as his villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.52,0:13:54.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was buried alive immediately\nafter I was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.66,0:13:56.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was placed in\na tiny coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.26,0:14:01.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My father must have been\nin a complete panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.10,0:14:06.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A judge with a promising future\nhaving a child by his lover?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.80,0:14:08.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That sort of thing\nis frowned upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.94,0:14:11.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So he sheltered my mother in the mansion\nat Auteuil, and he then took me and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.01,0:14:15.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your Honor! Perhaps we should\nadjourn for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.41,0:14:17.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The defendant will\nremain silent!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.18,0:14:21.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's obviously nothing but a blackmailer\nwho was hired by someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.05,0:14:23.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who hired you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.76,0:14:27.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is this any way to treat me? After all, we\nhaven't seen one another for 17 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.76,0:14:32.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The people enter into evidence the results of\NDNA testing on the defendant and the witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.08,0:14:46.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.11,0:14:51.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The coffin. The coffin that my parents\ngave to me instead of a crib.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.48,0:14:52.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, stop this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.69,0:14:56.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I beg of you! Please, no more!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.05,0:15:00.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What wonderful timing. Allow me\nto introduce my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.69,0:15:03.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is Baroness Victoria Danglars.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.60,0:15:07.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come now, Mother,\nisn't that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.13,0:15:10.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Father shoved me into this box\nand then buried me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.64,0:15:12.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...the garden behind the mansion,\ndidn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.75,0:15:32.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My boy... My darling baby!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.83,0:15:41.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me...\NPlease, forgive your mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.37,0:15:43.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Be quiet!\NShut up this instant!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.47,0:15:45.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's out of\nher mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.14,0:15:48.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Father! Don't say such things\nabout Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.27,0:15:49.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What a terrible thing\nto say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.64,0:15:53.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's him! He must be the one\nwho put you up to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.38,0:15:58.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your Honor, he made up this\nentire preposterous story!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.18,0:16:02.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How could it be otherwise? I mean,\nthat baby is dead and buried.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.39,0:16:05.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't possibly\nturn up and...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.42,0:16:09.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your Honor, please enter the defendant's\nstatement just now into the record.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.59,0:16:12.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No! I only meant that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.10,0:16:12.22,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Order!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.13,0:16:13.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have to listen to me! This is a trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.23,0:16:16.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You lousy con artist!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.91,0:16:28.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The servant who saved my life\nleft this scrap of cloth with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.31,0:16:32.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He must have wrapped me in this\nso that I wouldn't freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.85,0:16:37.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For my whole life, this has been the most\nimportant thing in the world to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.72,0:16:43.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,After all, this is the one thing\nthat connects me to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.56,0:16:49.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You... Are you really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.74,0:16:51.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.10,0:16:57.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But if I hadn't resorted to this, you never would\nhave accepted that I really was your son, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.08,0:17:03.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to meet you\nso badly, Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.19,0:17:10.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.36,0:17:14.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why, son?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.56,0:17:15.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.83,0:17:21.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you can kiss\nmy ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.77,0:17:26.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just looking at those haughty faces\nof yours makes me want to throw up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.97,0:17:30.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, you bastards are animals\nno different from him and me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.34,0:17:34.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You hide your filthy true natures\nbehind those clean masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.95,0:17:38.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You do! And you! And so do you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.99,0:17:54.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to recall a certain Monsieur Dantes\nliving here long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.77,0:17:59.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't really know. This place\nhas stood empty for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.55,0:18:09.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.22,0:18:17.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mercedes...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.76,0:18:26.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're still young... And something tells me\nthat my boy isn't coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.30,0:18:32.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't spend your whole life looking\nafter a doddering old man like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.00,0:18:35.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, you should go...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.47,0:18:37.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Summer is almost over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.71,0:18:40.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No! I won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.28,0:18:43.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He'll come back! I know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.39,0:18:50.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.36,0:18:54.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And how are we feeling? Better, I hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.56,0:18:58.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who are you?\NWhy are you doing this to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.96,0:19:01.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.03,0:19:07.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten the innocent man\nyou convicted 25 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.91,0:19:11.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...as the district judge\nfor Marseilles?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.64,0:19:16.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The instant you discovered\nyour own name in that letter,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.58,0:19:21.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...you decided to secretly\neliminate that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.02,0:19:23.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond Dantes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.49,0:19:26.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is that really you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.92,0:19:32.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The man who was once known by that name\ndied in the prison of the Chateau d'lf...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.06,0:19:35.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and returned to life\nas Gankutsuou.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.84,0:19:41.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That letter you were carrying\nwas too dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.37,0:19:46.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If I hadn't done something, the government\nwould have fallen into chaos!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.31,0:19:47.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I had no choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.18,0:19:51.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You are indeed a patriot,\NMonsieur Villefort!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.72,0:19:56.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, the real motive for your actions\nwas to protect yourself, was it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.99,0:20:00.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was to maintain\nlaw and order.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.89,0:20:04.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And that meritorious deed made you\nthe man you are right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.66,0:20:08.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was all for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.93,0:20:12.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, that needle\nwas coated with poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.00,0:20:13.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.84,0:20:15.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That poison will be\na blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.81,0:20:22.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It will rot your brain and will send you\nto a world where no one can convict you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.41,0:20:23.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.88,0:20:26.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No! Not that!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.02,0:20:30.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Villefort, poor servant\nof the law...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.09,0:20:36.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The wings of the law will gently\ncradle you until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.83,0:20:45.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And that makes two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.61,0:20:54.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Start walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.38,0:21:02.88,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eastern Fleet flagship\nhas crossed Rubicon Line!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.32,0:21:07.78,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Be advised. According to Article 59 of the\NMilitary Code, this is considered an act of...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.05,0:23:13.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In spite of everything, the past\nwill not let go of the men.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.72,0:23:17.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Vengeance gives rise to violence,\nand the cycle of sorrow continues.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.86,0:23:20.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Gankutsuou,\NThe Count of Monte Cristo act 22:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.04,0:23:21.46,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,352)}Act 22:\NCounterattack
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.46,0:23:21.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."Counterattack."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.73,0:23:24.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time,\nand hold out hope!
